Fantastic sushi, great sake and amazing atmosphere. Didn't have a single bad thing.

To much rice.on the hand roll and little fillings. I have the spycy tuna - they didn't remove the seed from the pepper so have it in your mouth, and I ask for a salmon avocado -thing that they don't have in the menu. There menu is not original and overpriced. But the service is very good
Great authentic sushi place. Excellent service
Best sushi I ever had. Fresh, tasty and good looking. Sit at the bar and talk to your sushi chef, while he makes your food.
Quite literally the best sushi I've ever had. Ask for the salmon belly, the uni and qual egg sushi, and the dancing shrimp. Can't go wrong.
Best mackerel I've ever had. Order shrimp too, it's a real show. Excellent fish, excellent service. This place is absolutely worth the price.
Great!
Basic menu and decor but great fresh food prepared right in front of you. Chefs engage customers at the bar offering friendly advice on what's best that day.
Place was great! HIROSHI was great!
Great food and service.
The most authentic sushi south of Torrence.
Poor service
Packed with Japanese people... Lived up to the expectation... I'll be back.
Great authentic Japanese food. I always get the omakaze.

A small sushi bar serving delicious Japanese fare. Sitting at the bar is a good choice, if you want to be entertained by the easy going sushi chefs. There is a good selection to sample at reasonable prices.

Wow! This place was absolutely amazing! It is expensive but I think it is worth every single penny. The sashimi was some of the best I have ever tasted in my entire life! I also tried a few pieces of my parties rolls and they were delicious as well. I think I have found my go to sushi spot in San Diego! Take is the bomb!
Great sushi place in the Gaslamp district. This was the best spicy tuna tartare that I've had (and not just because of the gold leaf). They did a really good job with the live Amaebi as well.

Really good sushi place with personable chefs at the bar.  I tend to get a soft shell crab roll (a.k.a. spider roll) and a spicy tuna roll at any sushi place I go, this place has a top-notch spicy tuna roll but the soft shell crab was just so-so.  Definitely get the fresh live tiger shrimp, it's a great part of the experience!

Great sushi, great service.  This place is really a fine establishment.  I went with some friends and we all couldn't get over how cute our waitress was, she was a real firecracker but that's neither here nor there.  If you are looking for a fun time on a cool California evening then this is your place!

The WORST service I have ever received in ANY restaurant!  We were seated in a timely manner, the sushi was good, not amazing, but over priced.  After we paid our bill our party of four was finishing up, and the owner asked us to leave!  She said she needed the table!  How rude!  I will not go back!!
Fantastic quality, great presentation and delicious recipes - but you will pay a "downtown premium".... The food was amazing, but too expensive for what you get.
Great chef recommendations. Friendly service.

After asking what was fresh, I was served several day old Spanish mackerel. The fish head and bones were provided as decoration and the cloudiness color in its eye clearly indicated it was several days old. Disappointing.

Not cheap (but would you want cheap sushi?)  They brew their own soy sauce which was different and very good.  Fresh was very fresh and the service was on point.  I make a point to go here at least twice every time I am in the area.

Decent sushi, nothing fancy but good. Parking, but limited space in the lot during the day. I don't know why I keep going there, maybe because im super hungry and it's so close to me? ya that's why, how ever I will keep you posted on a better sushi places around here. thank you
This place was recommended, and we were pleased.

sit at the sushi bar and leave your fate in the hands of the sushi chef for the best experience. the fish is fabulously fresh, and some interesting appetizers such as their wonderful monkfish liver keep things exciting. easily the best sushi in downtown.
